modules.description: This module provides functions to retrieve the current time as a POSIX timestamp split into days and picoseconds, the local time zone offset in seconds, and the clock's period in days and picoseconds. It works with integer and 64-bit integer types to represent time values with high precision. Concrete use cases include time-stamping events in distributed systems and calculating time intervals for scheduling or logging.

Provides access to a monotonic clock with nanosecond precision, returning time elapsed since an arbitrary starting point. Works with 64-bit integers to represent time values. Useful for measuring durations and profiling code execution in MirageOS environments.
